<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Coly, the reason why an enchanter would want 255 charisma is that they are more effective with the more charisma that they have. The higher their charisma... the more their mez spells stick... charm.. etc. I've seen some enchanters who sacrifice some int to have the higher charisma. At lvl 51 I have 200int and 217cha. The moment I pass 200int, I look to see what int enchanceing item I can take off and replace with charisma. The post earlier about the different items (can't remember who) is right though. Opalline Earrings, Crude Stein, the rings/bracers, all give great cha and are extremely cheap. These boots would be great for an enchanter with the 8cha. Anyone know their plat value by chance?</font></td></tr></table>
