<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Lozi, CT</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-15 04:55:06</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Max effective for int or wis is 200. The difference in mana between 200 and 210 int is much less than the difference between 190 and 200 (one mana per point after 200 is what I have heard). Stats can go higher than 255 BTW, they won't register higher than 255, but there is a difference for stats that are effective that high. No one who knows is saying exactly what the difference between having a 180 cha or a 220 cha for an enchanter is. An enchanter should aim for 200/200 with any extra on the cha side IMO. I've been playing cha vs int for spots I can equip items that are either since I was 30. Right now I usually run a 193 cha and a 158 int (at level 46). But if I don't have to do crowd control I run with 160 cha and 176 int. 5k is what an enchanter friend said he paid for these boots. The Hole is a very nasty place, I treat it like a plane/dragon raid and haven't had the chance to put a guild party together with the correct mix of people to go adventure there. I know a handful of people in AoW (who have gotten a lot of the items from the hole) and they say it's tough. Look at it as 2 groups 50+ that work well together to get deep into the Hole. </font></td></tr></table>
